ORDER BY last_update DESC;

external_knowledge:
- A patch can be considered "forwarded" when it is sent to another team for review or implementation; 
- The "cumulative access count" refers to the total number of times a patch has been accessed by users; 
- The "last update date" indicates when a patch was last modified or updated.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(patch_id) AS forwarded_patches_count
FROM patch_forwarding
WHERE status = 'completed';
